text: The Cathedral of Uppsala (), found in the city of Uppsala, Sweden, was built in the late 13th century. It is at a height and length of 118.7 m is the largest church building in Scandinavia. == Other websites == * Photos of Cathedral of Uppsala * Tourist guide * Official Uppland tourist page * Cathedral's website Category:Church of Sweden cathedrals Category:Uppsala Category:13th-century buildings and structures
title: Uppsala Cathedral
